What is CICR?
CICR (Creative & Innovative Cell in Robotics) is a robotics and innovation club at JIIT. We focus on hands-on projects in robotics, AI, and automation. Check out our website: https://cicr.in

What projects is CICR working on?

CICR’s projects include Robo-Soccer bots, Algo-Benchmaker (https://github.com/CICR-The-Robotics-Hub-of-JIIT-128/Algo-Benchmaker), line-following robots, and autonomous drones. Visit our GitHub for details!

What is Techtonic?

Techtonic is CICR’s annual 3-day robotics workshop for 1st-year students. You’ll learn ROS, Arduino, and build projects like line-following robots. Every year there is set of unique topics. Details: https://techtonic.cicr.in

What is Algo-Benchmaker?

Algo-Benchmaker (GitHub: https://github.com/CICR-The-Robotics-Hub-of-JIIT-128/Algo-Benchmaker) is a C++ toolbox to benchmark algorithms like A* and Dijkstra for robotics. It visualizes paths and compares performance metrics.
Explain the benchmarking tool

Algo-Benchmaker (GitHub: https://github.com/CICR-The-Robotics-Hub-of-JIIT-128/Algo-Benchmaker) is a C++ toolbox to benchmark algorithms like A* and Dijkstra for robotics. It visualizes paths and compares performance metrics.
How does the pathfinding tool work?

Algo-Benchmaker (GitHub: https://github.com/CICR-The-Robotics-Hub-of-JIIT-128/Algo-Benchmaker) is a C++ toolbox to benchmark algorithms like A* and Dijkstra for robotics. It visualizes paths and compares performance metrics.

How does CICR manage hardware?
Use inventory.cicr.in to reserve sensors, motors, and tools. Log in with your CICR credentials to check availability, though if you are not a club member than you need to contact the management team.
